# App logs

When the taskbar disappears, won't start, or "stopped", **read the app log first** before guessing.

## Location

- **Primary:** `~/Library/Logs/BetterMacTaskbar/app.log`
- **Rotated backup (when primary exceeds ~2MB):** `~/Library/Logs/BetterMacTaskbar/app.1.log`

```bash
tail -n 80 ~/Library/Logs/BetterMacTaskbar/app.log
pgrep -fl BetterMacTaskbar
```

## What to look for

| Line | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `bootstrap` / `application ready` | App launched successfully |
| `heartbeat` (every ~60s) | Process was still alive |
| `caughtSignal signal=SIGTERM` | Killed by `pkill` / quit signal (rebuild scripts do this) |
| `shutdown` / `applicationWillTerminate` | Clean quit (Start menu / status menu Quit) |
| `uncaughtException` | Swift/ObjC exception crash |
| Last heartbeat, then silence | Died via SIGKILL, forced quit, or crash with no handler |

Also check whether the process is running: `pgrep -x BetterMacTaskbar`.

## Logging API

Use `AppLog` (`Sources/Services/AppLog.swift`):

```swift
AppLog.info("something happened", ["key": value])
AppLog.error("failed", ["error": message])
```

Do **not** write debug/agent logs under `.cursor/debug-*.log` for production diagnosis — use `AppLog`.
